The paper discusses cryptographic protocols and their formal analysis, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also introduces a new notion of deduction systems, which is related to logic and formal methods (cs.LO). The paper also mentions decision procedures, which are related to information theory (cs.IT) and algorithms and data structures (cs.DS). Finally, the paper discusses the reduction of equivalence properties to reachability properties, which is related to programming languages and compilers (cs.PL).
